\sum_{k=0}^{n} \binom{n}{k}^2kp^k,
\sum_{k=0}^{n} k p^k \binom{n}{k}^2 = n^2 p \ _2F_1(1-n, 1-n, 2, p).
\frac{d}{dp}{}_2F_1(a,b,c,p)=\frac{ab}{c}{}_2F_1(a+1,b+1,c+1,p)
_2F_1(1-n,1-n,2,p)=\frac{1}{n^2}\frac{d}{dp}{}_2F_1(-n,-n,1,p).\tag{1}
_2F_1(1-n,1-n,2,p)=\frac{1}{n^2}\frac{d}{dp}\left[\left(1-p\right)^nP_n\left(\frac{1+p}{1-p}\right)\right],
\sum_{k=0}^n k p^k{n\choose k}^2=p\frac{d}{dp}\left[\left(1-p\right)^nP_n\left(\frac{1+p}{1-p}\right)\right].\tag{3}
\sum_{k=0}^n p^k{n\choose k}^2=\left(1-p\right)^nP_n\left(\frac{1+p}{1-p}\right). 
